SECTION 2: AUTHORIZED ACTIVITIES

  The testing team is authorized to perform the following:

  2.1 Social Engineering
      - In-person pretexting (IT technician, delivery, vendor)
      - Tailgating through secured doors
      - Shoulder surfing for credentials
      - Phone-based pretexting to gain physical access info

  2.2 Physical Bypass
      - Non-destructive lock picking
      - Badge cloning using captured credentials
      - Door latch manipulation
      - Accessing unlocked entry points

  2.3 Surveillance
      - Photography of security controls
      - Video recording (exterior only unless approved)
      - Documenting guard patrol patterns
      - Parking lot observation

  2.4 Device Deployment
      - USB drop devices (pre-approved payloads ONLY)
      - Rogue network devices (if approved in SOW)
      - Keyloggers (physical — if approved in SOW)

2.5 Found Credentials / Unlocked Access
      - Found badge/keys/passwords: Photograph, document, report to
        client immediately. Do NOT use without explicit written approval.
      - Unlocked doors after hours: Document, report, do NOT enter
        without approval.
      - Shoulder-surfed credentials: Document only; use only if client
        approves in writing.

